install swaync on linux hyprland
To install and set up Sway Notification Center (SwayNC) on Hyprland, follow these steps to replace any existing notification daemons and ensure it starts automatically. 
1. Install SwayNC
Use your distribution's package manager to install the package. Note that on some systems, it is listed as sway-notification-center. 
GitHub
GitHub
Arch Linux: sudo pacman -S swaync (or use yay -S swaync-git for the AUR version).
Fedora: Enable the COPR repository first:
sudo dnf copr enable erikreider/SwayNotificationCenter
sudo dnf install SwayNotificationCenter.
Ubuntu/Debian: sudo apt install sway-notification-center.
openSUSE Tumbleweed: sudo zypper install SwayNotificationCenter. 
