2. Disable Existing Daemons
Only one notification daemon can run at a time. If you have Mako or Dunst installed, they may block SwayNC from acquiring the notification name. 
Reddit
Reddit
Remove Mako: sudo pacman -R mako (on Arch) or equivalent for your distro.
Alternatively, ensure they are not set to autostart in your config files. 
3. Autostart in Hyprland 
To have SwayNC start every time you log into Hyprland, add the following line to your ~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf file:
bash
exec-once = swaync
Use code with caution.

